parameters.rationale: Baseline reference: default rank and LR with standard local steps to benchmark improvements.
Aggressive LR with tighter projection to speed convergence while limiting drift via fewer local steps; tests low-comm regime.
Higher rank for capacity and potential accuracy gains, paired with conservative LR for stability without momentum.
Moderate rank with more local steps to probe drift/efficiency trade-offs; checks if projection-only benefits persist.
Minimal rank to reduce communication and noise; conservative LR to mitigate underfitting risks from very tight subspace.
Higher capacity and faster LR to improve accuracy while reducing drift with fewer local steps; tests fast-yet-stable updates.
Conservative LR for maximum stability without momentum; moderate rank to balance capacity and communication.
